Soak raisins in coffee until plump. Do not drain. Cream together the shortening, sugar and eggs. Blend in molasses and vanilla. In a large bowl mix together the cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, ginger, flour, baking soda, and salt. Make a well in the center of the bowl. Add the liquid ingredients to the well in the dry ingredients. Stir in coffee with raisins and nuts. Pour batter into a greased 9x5 inch loaf pan. Bake in a preheated 350 degree F(175 degrees C) oven for one hour.